    summaryEn: 'Sixth Western Han emperor who crushed the Rebellion of the Seven States and continued the Wen-Jing prosperity.',
    description: '刘启继承父亲文帝的基业，继续休养生息政策。但他面临诸侯王势力坐大的危机——前154年，以吴王刘濞为首的七国发动叛乱。景帝在周亚夫等人辅佐下仅三个月便平定叛乱，随后大规模削减诸侯王的封地和权力，中央集权显著加强。他的统治与文帝合称「文景之治」，为后来的武帝盛世铺平了道路。',
    descriptionEn: 'Liu Qi continued his father\'s laissez-faire policies. When the Rebellion of the Seven States erupted in 154 BCE led by the Prince of Wu, he crushed it within three months with the help of general Zhou Yafu. He then systematically reduced princely territories and powers, significantly strengthening central authority. Together with his father\'s reign, this era of peace and prosperity set the stage for Emperor Wu\'s great campaigns.',
