    summary: '南宋开国皇帝赵构，在金兵追击下渡江南逃，偏安临安，以莫须有罪名杀害岳飞。',
    summaryEn: 'Founder of Southern Song who fled south across the Yangtze from Jurchen pursuers, settled in Lin\'an, and executed the general Yue Fei on fabricated charges.',
    description: '赵构是徽宗第九子，靖康之变中侥幸未被掳走。他在应天府（商丘）即位后一路南逃——从扬州到镇江到杭州到明州甚至海上——直到金兵北撤。定都临安（杭州）后他始终主和，重用秦桧，在岳飞连战连捷时用十二道金牌将其召回，最终以「莫须有」罪名处死。他的偏安政策稳固了南宋政权，但也永远放弃了收复中原的希望。',
    descriptionEn: 'Zhao Gou, Huizong\'s ninth son, was the only prince to escape the Jingkang capture. Proclaimed emperor at Shangqiu, he fled south — from Yangzhou to Zhenjiang to Hangzhou to Mingzhou and even to sea — until the Jurchens retreated. After settling at Lin\'an (Hangzhou), he consistently prioritized peace, employing Qin Hui and recalling Yue Fei with twelve gold medallions just as the general was on the verge of victory, ultimately executing him on \'dubious\' charges. His policy of accommodation preserved the Southern Song state but forever abandoned hope of reclaiming the north.',
    alternativeNames: ['赵构', 'Zhao Gou'],
