    summary: '清朝第五位皇帝胤禛，以铁腕著称，整顿吏治、改革财政，为乾隆盛世奠定基础。',
    summaryEn: 'Fifth Qing emperor known for iron-fisted rule; he reformed governance and state finances, laying the foundation for the Qianlong era.',
    description: '胤禛在残酷的储位之争中胜出——「九子夺嫡」是清朝最激烈的皇位争夺。他以勤政著称——据说每天批阅奏章至深夜，朱批字数常常超过奏章本身。他推行了摊丁入亩、耗羡归公、改土归流等重大改革，设立军机处强化皇权，清查贪腐毫不手软。他的13年统治以其严格和不妥协著称——他不是最讨人喜欢的皇帝，但很可能是清朝最有效率的皇帝。',
    descriptionEn: 'Yinzhen prevailed in the brutal succession struggle — the \'Nine Princes\' Contest\' was Qing\'s most intense power battle. He was legendary for diligence, reportedly reviewing memorials into the night and writing vermilion rescripts longer than the original submissions. His major reforms — amalgamating the head tax into land tax, returning surcharges to the state treasury, and replacing native chieftains with imperial officials — together with creating the Grand Council to strengthen imperial authority and relentlessly pursuing corruption. His 13-year reign was defined by rigor and uncompromise — not the most likable emperor, but arguably Qing\'s most effective one.',
