    summaryEn: 'The allied forces of Sun Quan and Liu Bei decisively defeated Cao Cao\'s much larger army at Red Cliffs, establishing the foundation for the Three Kingdoms and becoming one of China\'s most celebrated battles.',
    description: '建安十三年（208年），曹操基本统一北方后挥师南下，号称八十万大军（实际约二十余万），意欲一举吞并江南。在诸葛亮与鲁肃的斡旋下，孙权和刘备结成同盟。周瑜率三万水军在赤壁（今湖北赤壁）与曹军相遇，利用火攻战术，借助东南风点燃曹军连环战船。此役曹军大败，死伤无数，曹操被迫退回北方。赤壁之战后，孙权稳固了江东基业，刘备趁机夺取荆州并向益州发展，三足鼎立格局基本形成。此战因《三国演义》的文学渲染而家喻户晓。',
    descriptionEn: 'In the winter of 208 CE, after unifying most of northern China, Cao Cao marched south with a force claimed to be 800,000 (actually around 200,000-250,000), intending to conquer the south. Through the diplomacy of Zhuge Liang and Lu Su, Sun Quan and Liu Bei formed an alliance. Zhou Yu led 30,000 naval troops to confront Cao Cao at Red Cliffs and employed a fire attack: taking advantage of the southeast wind, fire ships were sent into Cao\'s chained fleet. Cao Cao\'s forces were routed with massive casualties, forcing him to retreat north. After Red Cliffs, Sun Quan consolidated his position in Jiangdong, Liu Bei seized Jing Province and expanded into Yi Province, and the tripartite balance of the Three Kingdoms took shape. The battle gained legendary status through its romanticized portrayal in "Romance of the Three Kingdoms."',
