    summary: '教皇格里高利九世建立教廷宗教裁判所，系统性地调查和审判异端，对中世纪欧洲的宗教和思想产生了深远影响。',
    summaryEn: 'Pope Gregory IX established the Papal Inquisition, systematically investigating and trying heresy, with profound consequences for medieval European religion and thought.',
    description: '1231年，教皇格里高利九世颁布《绝罚令》（Excommunicamus），正式建立直属教廷的宗教裁判所制度，授权经过专门训练的多明我会和方济各会修士担任裁判官，系统性地调查、审判和惩罚异端。裁判所主要针对清洁派（卡特里派）和瓦勒度派等被视为威胁教会统一的异端运动。裁判程序包括调查、告发、审讯和判决，被定罪者可被移交给世俗当局处以火刑。宗教裁判所持续数百年，后来在西班牙（1478年建立）和葡萄牙发展成更为严酷的国家机构。值得注意的是，中世纪宗教裁判所的实际处决数量远低于后来的历史想象，但其对思想自由和宗教宽容的压制产生了深远的历史影响。',
    descriptionEn: 'In 1231, Pope Gregory IX issued the bull "Excommunicamus," formally establishing the Papal Inquisition. He authorized specially trained Dominican and Franciscan friars as inquisitors to systematically investigate, judge, and punish heresy. The Inquisition primarily targeted the Cathars and Waldensians, movements seen as threatening church unity. Its procedures involved investigation, denunciation, interrogation, and sentencing; those convicted could be handed over to secular authorities for execution by burning. The Inquisition persisted for centuries, later developing into harsher national institutions in Spain (established 1478) and Portugal. Notably, medieval inquisitorial executions were far fewer than later historical imagination suggests, but the institution\'s suppression of freedom of thought and religious tolerance had profound historical consequences.',
