    description: '源平合战（1180-1185年）是日本史上最著名的内战之一，源赖朝与其弟源义经率领的源氏（关东武士）对抗平清盛建立的平氏政权。战争始于以仁王和平氏叛乱的号召。1184年，源义经在一之谷战役中奇袭大败平氏；1185年3月，在关门海峡的坛之浦海战中，源氏水军利用潮汐变化最终全歼平氏舰队，年仅8岁的安德天皇被外祖母抱着投海自尽，平氏彻底灭亡。源赖朝随后以镰仓为基地建立了日本第一个武士政权。平家物语以文学形式记录了这场战争的始末，成为日本文学经典，深刻地塑造了日本人的"无常"观。',
    descriptionEn: 'The Genpei War (1180-1185) was one of Japan\'s most famous civil conflicts, pitting Minamoto no Yoritomo and his brother Yoshitsune\'s eastern samurai against the Taira regime founded by Taira no Kiyomori. The war erupted following Prince Mochihito\'s call to arms. In 1184, Yoshitsune achieved a stunning surprise victory at Ichi-no-Tani. In March 1185, at the naval battle of Dan-no-ura in the Shimonoseki Strait, the Minamoto fleet exploited tidal currents to annihilate the Taira fleet; the 8-year-old Emperor Antoku was drowned by his grandmother to prevent capture. The Taira clan was extinguished. Yoritomo then established Japan\'s first samurai government at Kamakura. "The Tale of the Heike," the literary record of this war, became a Japanese classic that profoundly shaped the Japanese aesthetic of impermanence (mono no aware).',
