    summary: '结束三十年战争的系列和约，确立了近代国家主权原则，被称为威斯特伐利亚体系，是现代国际关系体系的奠基之作。',
    summaryEn: 'The series of treaties ending the Thirty Years\' War established the principle of state sovereignty and created the Westphalian system, foundational to modern international relations.',
    description: '1648年，经过长达四年的谈判，三十年战争（1618-1648）各参战国在威斯特伐利亚的两个城市签署了系列和约：《明斯特和约》和《奥斯纳布吕克和约》。和约确立了若干对后世影响深远的原则：各国对其领土拥有完全主权（不得干涉内政）、国家在法律上平等、"教随国定"（cuius regio, eius religio）的扩大版确认了教派共存。神圣罗马帝国实际上解体为300多个独立邦国，荷兰和瑞士的独立得到正式承认，法国和瑞典获得大片领土并成为欧洲大国。威斯特伐利亚体系通常被视为现代民族国家和国际法体系的起点。',
    descriptionEn: 'In 1648, after four years of negotiation, the combatants of the Thirty Years\' War (1618-1648) signed a series of treaties in two Westphalian cities: the Peace of Münster and the Peace of Osnabrück. The treaties established several principles with far-reaching consequences: states hold full sovereignty over their territories (non-interference in domestic affairs), legal equality among states, and an expanded version of "cuius regio, eius religio" confirming confessional coexistence. The Holy Roman Empire was effectively dissolved into over 300 independent states; Dutch and Swiss independence received formal recognition; France and Sweden gained substantial territories and emerged as European great powers. The Westphalian system is generally regarded as the starting point of the modern nation-state and international legal order.',
