    description: '七年战争（1756-1763）是一场真正的全球性冲突，交战遍及欧洲、北美（法国-印第安人战争）、印度（第三次卡那提克战争）、加勒比海、西非和菲律宾。在欧洲大陆，普鲁士的腓特烈大帝以惊人的军事才能对抗法、奥、俄三国的联合进攻；在海外，英国皇家海军逐步夺取法国殖民地。1763年的《巴黎和约》使英国获得加拿大、密西西比河以东的北美领土、佛罗里达以及在印度的优势地位，从此成为世界头号殖民帝国。法国丧失了大部分海外殖民地，其巨额战争债务也成为法国大革命的重要财政背景。年轻时代的乔治·华盛顿在此战的北美战场上初次崭露头角。',
    descriptionEn: 'The Seven Years\' War (1756-1763) was a truly global conflict fought across Europe, North America (the French and Indian War), India (the Third Carnatic War), the Caribbean, West Africa, and the Philippines. On the European continent, Prussia\'s Frederick the Great displayed astonishing military skill against the combined onslaught of France, Austria, and Russia. Overseas, Britain\'s Royal Navy systematically seized French colonies. The 1763 Treaty of Paris granted Britain Canada, all North American territory east of the Mississippi, Florida, and a dominant position in India, making it the world\'s foremost colonial empire. France lost most of its overseas possessions, and its enormous war debt became a crucial financial background to the French Revolution. A young George Washington first gained military experience and reputation in the North American theater of this war.',
