    summaryEn: 'The Philadelphia Constitutional Convention drafted the world\'s first written constitution, establishing separation of powers and federalism as a model for constitutions worldwide.',
    description: '1787年5月至9月，55名各州代表在费城独立厅召开制宪会议，由乔治·华盛顿主持。会议摒弃了原来的《邦联条例》，起草了全新的联邦宪法，建立了三权分立的政府架构：立法权归国会（参众两院），行政权归总统，司法权归最高法院和下级联邦法院。在联邦派（汉密尔顿、麦迪逊）和反联邦派之间激烈辩论后，1788年宪法经足够数量的州批准后生效。1789年国会通过了十条宪法修正案即《权利法案》，保障言论、宗教、持枪等基本自由。美国宪法至今仅通过27条修正案，其持久性和适应性使其成为现代宪政民主制度最具影响力的范本之一。',
    descriptionEn: 'From May to September 1787, 55 delegates from the states convened at Independence Hall in Philadelphia under George Washington\'s presidency. They abandoned the Articles of Confederation and drafted a new federal constitution establishing a tripartite government: legislative power to Congress (bicameral House and Senate), executive power to the President, and judicial power to the Supreme Court and inferior federal courts. After intense debate between Federalists (Hamilton, Madison) and Anti-Federalists, the Constitution was ratified by a sufficient number of states in 1788. In 1789, Congress passed ten amendments as the Bill of Rights, protecting freedoms of speech, religion, and bearing arms. With only 27 amendments to date, the US Constitution\'s durability and adaptability have made it one of the most influential models of modern constitutional democracy.',
