    summary: '法国第三等级代表在网球场庄严宣誓制定宪法，是法国大革命中最具象征意义的开端事件之一。',
    summaryEn: 'The Third Estate deputies swore a solemn oath in a tennis court to draft a constitution, one of the most symbolically powerful inaugural acts of the French Revolution.',
    description: '1789年6月20日早晨，当国民议会的代表们抵达凡尔赛宫的会议室时，发现大门紧锁，卫兵严守——国王试图以闭门手段阻止第三等级的行动。代表们在拜伊的带领下转移到附近的皇家室内网球场。在这间简陋的大厅内，577名代表中的576人举起右手，庄严宣誓："在任何必要的地点继续集会，直到王国宪法被制定出来并在坚实的基础上确立"。唯一的弃权者是代表约瑟夫·马丁-道什。这一宣誓不仅是第三等级对王权的公开挑战，更是法国历史上主权从君主向国民转移的标志性时刻。画家雅克-路易·大卫的未完成名作《网球场宣誓》（1791年）使这一场景永载史册。',
    descriptionEn: 'On the morning of June 20, 1789, deputies of the National Assembly arrived at their meeting hall in Versailles only to find the doors locked and guarded—the king\'s attempt to obstruct the Third Estate. Led by Jean-Sylvain Bailly, the deputies moved to the nearby Royal Tennis Court. In this austere hall, 576 of the 577 deputies raised their right hands and swore a solemn oath "to continue meeting wherever circumstances require until the constitution of the kingdom is established on solid foundations." The lone dissenter was deputy Joseph Martin-Dauch. This oath was not merely a public challenge to royal authority but a landmark moment in the transfer of sovereignty from monarch to nation in French history. Jacques-Louis David\'s unfinished masterpiece "The Tennis Court Oath" (1791) immortalized the scene.',
