    summary: '拿破仑亲自参与制定的《法国民法典》，确立法律面前人人平等、契约自由和私有财产不可侵犯等原则，影响全球法律体系。',
    summaryEn: 'The French Civil Code, personally shaped by Napoleon, established equality before the law, freedom of contract, and inviolable private property, influencing legal systems worldwide.',
    description: '1804年3月21日，法兰西第一帝国正式颁布了《法国民法典》（后称拿破仑法典）。拿破仑本人亲自主持了法典编纂委员会的一百多次会议，将其军事效率和清晰思维注入立法之中。这部法典以清晰简洁的法文写就，共2281条，涵盖人法、物法和取得财产的各种方式三大部分。它确立了法律面前人人平等、世俗婚姻制度、契约自由、私有财产的绝对保护等原则。随着拿破仑军队的征战，这部法典被推广至欧洲大陆、拉丁美洲、中东和北非等地区，成为荷兰、意大利、西班牙、葡萄牙等国民法典的蓝本。即使到今天，全球仍有约四分之一的法律体系直接或间接受其影响。拿破仑曾说："我真正的荣耀不是打了四十场胜仗，而是民法典。"',
    descriptionEn: 'On March 21, 1804, the First French Empire officially promulgated the French Civil Code (later the Napoleonic Code). Napoleon personally presided over more than a hundred sessions of the drafting commission, infusing military efficiency and clarity of thought into the legislation. Written in clear, concise French, the Code\'s 2,281 articles covered three books: persons, property, and acquisition of property. It established equality before the law, secular marriage, freedom of contract, and absolute protection of private property. As Napoleonic armies conquered Europe, the Code spread across the continent, Latin America, the Middle East, and North Africa, becoming the model for civil codes in the Netherlands, Italy, Spain, Portugal, and beyond. Even today, roughly a quarter of the world\'s legal systems are directly or indirectly influenced by it. Napoleon himself reflected: "My true glory is not having won forty battles; Waterloo will efface the memory of so many victories. What nothing will efface, what will live eternally, is my Civil Code."',
