    summaryEn: 'The largest and bloodiest battle of the American Civil War, which shattered the Confederacy\'s last invasion of the North and inspired Lincoln\'s immortal Gettysburg Address.',
    description: '1863年7月1日至3日，在南军将领罗伯特·李将军试图入侵北方的决定性战役中，约16万人在宾夕法尼亚州葛底斯堡交战三天。战役的关键时刻是7月3日的"皮克特冲锋"——李将军命令乔治·皮克特率约12500名南军士兵跨越开阔地向北军阵地的中心发起正面进攻。冲锋以惨败告终，南军损失过半，李被迫率残部撤回弗吉尼亚。此役南北双方伤亡约5万人，是美洲大陆有史以来最惨烈的战斗。同年11月19日，林肯在葛底斯堡国家公墓落成典礼上发表了仅两分钟、十个句子的演说，以"民有、民治、民享的政府"的承诺重新定义了美国内战的根本意义。',
    descriptionEn: 'From July 1 to 3, 1863, in the decisive battle of Confederate General Robert E. Lee\'s attempted invasion of the North, approximately 160,000 men fought for three days at Gettysburg, Pennsylvania. The battle\'s climax came on July 3 with "Pickett\'s Charge"—Lee ordered George Pickett to lead about 12,500 Confederate soldiers in a frontal assault across open ground against the center of the Union line. The charge ended in catastrophe, with over half the attackers killed or wounded. Lee was forced to retreat to Virginia. Combined casualties numbered roughly 50,000, making Gettysburg the bloodiest battle ever fought on the American continent. On November 19, Lincoln delivered a two-minute, ten-sentence address at the dedication of the Soldiers\' National Cemetery, redefining the war\'s meaning with the promise of "government of the people, by the people, for the people."',
