    descriptionEn: 'In the early hours of June 6, 1944, under Supreme Commander General Eisenhower, Operation Overlord commenced. Over 150,000 Allied troops—American, British, Canadian, and others—landed simultaneously on five Normandy beachheads codenamed Utah, Omaha, Gold, Juno, and Sword. The night before, 24,000 paratroopers had been dropped behind German lines. Omaha Beach met the fiercest German resistance and suffered the heaviest American casualties. Nevertheless, by day\'s end the Allies had established five precarious beachheads. In the ensuing Normandy campaign, the Allies broke through Hitler\'s "Atlantic Wall" at great cost, liberating Paris on August 25. Simultaneously on the Eastern Front, the Soviets launched the colossal Operation Bagration (the Byelorussian Offensive), splitting German forces irreparably between two fronts.',
