    summaryEn: 'David Ben-Gurion declared the establishment of the State of Israel, immediately triggering war with neighboring Arab states and inaugurating the enduring Middle East conflict.',
    description: '1948年5月14日下午4时，在特拉维夫博物馆，犹太代办处主席戴维·本-古里安宣读了《以色列建国宣言》，宣布"在以色列地建立一个犹太国家——以色列国"。宣言发表后仅11分钟，美国总统杜鲁门即予以承认。次日（5月15日），埃及、约旦、叙利亚、黎巴嫩和伊拉克五国联军随即入侵新生的以色列国，第一次中东战争（以色列称独立战争，阿拉伯方面称大灾难/纳克巴）爆发。经过数月激战，以色列不仅守住了联合国1947年分治决议划出的犹太国领土，还额外控制了约60%的分配给阿拉伯国的土地。战争造成约70万巴勒斯坦阿拉伯人流离失所。以色列的建国和由此产生的阿以冲突在此后七十余年中深刻影响了中东地缘政治格局。',
    descriptionEn: 'At 4:00 PM on May 14, 1948, in the Tel Aviv Museum, Jewish Agency chairman David Ben-Gurion read the Declaration of the Establishment of the State of Israel, proclaiming "the establishment of a Jewish state in Eretz-Israel, to be known as the State of Israel." US President Truman granted recognition just 11 minutes after the declaration. The next day (May 15), the armies of Egypt, Jordan, Syria, Lebanon, and Iraq invaded, launching the First Arab-Israeli War. After months of fierce fighting, Israel not only held the territory allocated to the Jewish state under the UN\'s 1947 Partition Plan but additionally controlled about 60% of the land assigned to the proposed Arab state. The war displaced approximately 700,000 Palestinian Arabs. The establishment of Israel and the resulting Arab-Israeli conflict have profoundly shaped Middle Eastern geopolitics for over seven decades.',
